{"questionId":"26739","questionHtml":"<p>Find the vectors <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> and/or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(one vector to the line is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>c</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;therefore)&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>c</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>the line goes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> up for every <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> across</p>\n<p>(so the direction vector is)&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>m</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Although these are the most likely answers, many others are possible.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26739","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ2.15a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the vectors a and b in terms of m and/or c.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.11—Vector equation of a line in 2d and 3d"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}